            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/772/1*B2SACtTiN3AT8_C9gNg1QA.png" /></figure><p>We are happy to introduce a new plugin for WordPressâ€Šâ€”â€Š<a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/surveyjs/">SurveyJS plugin</a>. It will help you create a survey, quiz or form. Add it to any page or post on your WordPress site, collect results, and download them toÂ analyze.</p><p>The plugin is free and is released under the <a href="https://wordpress.org/about/license/">GPLv2</a> WordPress standard license. Registration is not requiredâ€Šâ€”â€Šsimply install and use it. It is based on SureveyJS libraries and uses a full SurveyJSÂ power.</p><h4>Here a short list of <em>SurveyJS features:</em></h4><ul><li>The plugin has 15 elements (questions and panels): from simple inputs like text and a dropdown to Panel containers and a dynamic matrix (table) to build complexÂ forms</li><li>Multi pageÂ support</li><li>Localization for many languages and support for multi language surveys/forms (one survey for several languages)</li><li>Control of survey flow: the ability to set visibility expressions for pages, panels, questions, and even individual items in checkboxes, radio groups, and dropdowns</li><li>The ability to fill data for checkboxes, radio groups, and dropdowns from webÂ services</li><li>User input validation with several built-in validators</li><li>The ability to show results in a read-only survey</li><li>Several good-looking themes and muchÂ more</li></ul><h4>Powerfull Editor</h4><p>You can build a survey by using a powerful visual editor called SurveyJS Builder. It can create a survey from scratch, customize it, and test your survey before you publish it on yourÂ site.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*D74SoTkJ-YpjzXVowYtLxw.png" /><figcaption>SurveyJS Builder</figcaption></figure><h4>How to add a survey to yourÂ site</h4><p>After the SurveyJS WordPress plugin is installed, you can open a list of available surveys. Here, create a new survey, open the editor window for any survey, open the survey results window, and delete the survey if youÂ want.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*QmudAE-RgLvkMmurAJLo_Q.png" /></figure><p>Press the â€œAdd Surveyâ€ button and the plugin will create a new survey and open it in the survey builderÂ window:</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*3NHb_52N-hWisGtzk5-SWQ.png" /></figure><p>You can easily drag and drop questions from the toolbox on the left side to the design surface and set properties by using the property grid on the right side of inplace editing tools. Each change is immediately saved, and you can undo it via the corresponding button in the top center part of theÂ editor.</p><p>More information about options and settings can be found in the <a href="https://surveyjs.io/Documentation/Builder/">documentation</a>.</p><p>After your survey is designed, we can add it to any page of your site via the â€œAdd Surveyâ€ button (Wordpress shortcode) in the PostsÂ section:</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*kj-J6vzqyYmTxo2GKmTARw.png" /></figure><p>You will see your survey in page preview mode and can take it. Voila! Weâ€™ve doneÂ it!</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*xUgeQga6gLlZVoLsNb33Lg.png" /></figure><p>What about results?â€Šâ€”â€Šyou are askingâ€¦ The survey results window is available on the surveys list via â€œResultsâ€:</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*8ejId3k3B0oCDTPaXb6l5w.png" /></figure><p>You can sort results, search against them, and export them in the most popularÂ format.</p><h4>Support, bug fixed and newÂ releases</h4><p><a href="https://github.com/surveyjs/surveyjs">SurveyJS </a>is a popular platform that helps you create surveys, quizzes, and forms in JavaScript. This plugin is a part of Project SurveyJS and will b